  '<p>Returns a CA instance with <code>initCA()</code> (idempotent — generates if missing), <code>signClientCert(opts)</code>, <code>revoke(certFingerprint)</code>, <code>status()</code>. <code>caKeySealedMode: "required"</code> refuses to write the plaintext PEM to disk — the CA private key only ever lives in <code>ca.key.enc</code> sealed under the vault. <code>"auto"</code> picks whichever form exists. <code>"disabled"</code> forces plaintext for environments without a vault passphrase. The pluggable engine lets operators swap to an HSM-backed signer or an externally-managed CA without rewriting consumers.</p>',
